The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Another hat for BCA chief
 BY OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT Calcutta: Bihar Cricket Association (BCA) president Amitabh Choudhary who is posted as DIG (SB) in Ranchi, has been given additional charge by the Jharkhand government. Now, Choudhary will also be doubling-up as director of sports, youth and culture. Im quite excited about this additional responsibility and, clearly, Ill be looking to make the 2007 National Games a huge success, Choudhary told The Telegraph Thursday, while speaking from Ranchi.  Copyright 
